    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-11-07T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-11-07T19:00:00-05:00" n="779"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d779">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">330/11–750: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">United States Mission</gloss> at the United
                        Nations</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-11-07T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 7, 1950—7 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>482. In order that there be left no doubt in Chi Commie mind whether US or UN has
                    any intention of aggression against Chi and so that public record is clear,
                        <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> believes there shld be inserted new
                    penultimate para in SC res,<note n="1" xml:id="d779fn1">See telegram 477,
                        November 5, 11 p. m., to New York, <ref target="#pg_1049">p.
                        1049</ref>.</note> following “Calls upon” para, along fol lines:</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“Affirms that if the Chi withdraw and refrain from intervention against UN
                        forces, the Chi frontier with Kor will be held inviolate by UN forces and
                        Chi’s legitimate interests in the frontier will be fully protected by the
                        UN.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
